The paper deals with machine learning techniques for autonomous driving, specifically imitation learning and latent variable models. This suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, given the focus on deep learning and probabilistic models, cs.LG is the most likely category. The use of computer vision for perception and control also makes cs.CV a likely category. The paper also deals with safety and robustness, which could place it under cs.SY and cs.RO. Finally, the use of high-level commands suggests a connection to cs.AI.
